	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A group of armed thieves robbed two G4S guards at a shopping centre in Boksburg on last Tuesday. Watch.WATCH A group of robbers unsuccessfully attempted to steal money from a cash-in-transit vehicle in Cape Town on Monday, national police said. The gang fired shots at the vehicle on the N2 highway heading towards Khayelitsha, said spokesperson Brigadier Vish Naidoo. He said a shootout ensued after the police's arrival at the scene. Nothing was taken and the group fled. No one was injured.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  